---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="LangGraph Checkpointer for SAP HANA — ~/stubborncoder"
  description="langgraph-checkpoint-hana: persistent memory, fault recovery, and time travel for LangGraph agents on HANA Cloud."
  activeLink="writing"
>

<section class="post-hero">
  <div class="post-hero-bg"></div>
  <div class="post-hero-overlay"></div>
  <div class="post-hero-content wrap">
    <a href="/#writing" class="post-back reveal">&#8592; Back to writing</a>

    <div class="post-meta-top reveal">
      <span>February 2026</span>
      <span>&middot;</span>
      <span>5 min read</span>
      <span class="source-badge">LinkedIn</span>
      <span class="source-badge source-badge--sap">SAP Community</span>
    </div>

    <h1 class="reveal">LangGraph Checkpointer<br>for <span class="em">SAP HANA Cloud</span></h1>

    <p class="post-subtitle reveal">
      Persistent memory, fault recovery, and time travel for your LangGraph agents —
      all in the HANA instance you already have.
    </p>

    <div class="post-tags-row reveal">
      <span class="post-tag post-tag--ember">LangGraph</span>
      <span class="post-tag post-tag--gold">SAP HANA</span>
      <span class="post-tag">AI Agents</span>
      <span class="post-tag">Open Source</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<main class="wrap">
  <article class="article">

    <h2 class="reveal">The missing piece</h2>

    <p class="reveal">
      LangGraph has checkpointers for PostgreSQL, SQLite, Redis, CosmosDB. The community
      added Snowflake and Couchbase. SAP HANA? Nothing.
    </p>

    <p class="reveal">
      So I built one.
    </p>

    <p class="reveal">
      If you're already using HANA Vector Store for RAG, your agent state can live in the
      same database. No separate Postgres or Redis just for checkpointing. One database,
      one connection, one place to manage.
    </p>

    <h2 class="reveal">langgraph-checkpoint-hana</h2>

    <p class="reveal">
      <code>langgraph-checkpoint-hana</code> implements the full <code>BaseCheckpointSaver</code>
      interface for HANA Cloud. It gives your LangGraph agents three critical capabilities:
    </p>

    <div class="features-grid reveal">
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">&#9881;</div>
        <div class="feature-title">Persistent memory</div>
        <div class="feature-desc">Agent state survives restarts and deployments. Conversations pick up where they left off.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">&#9889;</div>
        <div class="feature-title">Fault recovery</div>
        <div class="feature-desc">If an agent crashes mid-execution, it recovers from the last checkpoint — no lost work.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="feature-card">
        <div class="feature-icon">&#8634;</div>
        <div class="feature-title">Time travel</div>
        <div class="feature-desc">Replay agent execution from any previous state. Debug, audit, or branch from past decisions.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="code-block reveal">
      <span class="code-label">Installation</span>
      <span class="keyword">pip install</span> langgraph-checkpoint-hana
    </div>

    <h2 class="reveal">Implementation details</h2>

    <p class="reveal">
      The implementation uses <code>UPSERT WITH PRIMARY KEY</code> for atomic writes — no
      race conditions on concurrent checkpoint saves. Setup is straightforward with
      <code>from_conn_info()</code> and <code>from_env()</code> for easy container deployment.
    </p>

    <p class="reveal">
      I also added <code>delete_thread()</code> for GDPR cleanup — when a user requests data
      deletion, you can wipe their agent conversation history cleanly.
    </p>

    <blockquote class="reveal">
      <p>Async delegates to sync because hdbcli is synchronous — no point pretending otherwise.</p>
    </blockquote>

    <p class="reveal">
      One honest design choice: the async interface delegates to sync operations because
      HANA's Python driver (<code>hdbcli</code>) is synchronous. Rather than adding fake
      async wrappers that just run sync code in a thread pool, I kept it transparent.
      The interface is async-compatible for LangGraph, but the I/O is honest about what
      it's doing.
    </p>

    <div class="takeaway reveal">
      <div class="takeaway-label">Key points</div>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Full BaseCheckpointSaver</strong> — complete LangGraph interface implementation</li>
        <li><strong>Atomic writes</strong> — UPSERT WITH PRIMARY KEY prevents race conditions</li>
        <li><strong>Container-ready</strong> — from_env() reads connection info from environment variables</li>
        <li><strong>GDPR cleanup</strong> — delete_thread() for data deletion compliance</li>
        <li><strong>No extra infra</strong> — checkpoint data lives alongside your RAG vectors in HANA</li>
        <li><strong>MIT licensed</strong> — submitted to LangGraph as community checkpointer</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="article-footer reveal">
      <div class="article-footer-label">Resources</div>
      <div class="resource-links">
        <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/feed/update/urn:li:activity:7432392566404182016/" target="_blank" class="original-link">Read on LinkedIn &#8594;</a>
        <a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/artificial-intelligence-blogs-posts/langgraph-checkpoint-saver-for-sap-hana-cloud/ba-p/14336448" target="_blank" class="original-link original-link--sap">SAP Community &#8594;</a>
        <a href="https://github.com/stubborncoder/langgraph-checkpoint-hana" target="_blank" class="original-link original-link--gh">GitHub &#8594;</a>
      </div>
    </div>

  </article>

  <section class="more-posts">
    <div class="more-posts-title">More writing</div>
    <a href="/blog/semantic-caching-hana" class="more-row">
      <span class="more-date">2026.03</span>
      <span class="more-title">Semantic Caching for SAP HANA Cloud</span>
      <span class="more-src">LinkedIn</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/blog/hybrid-retrieval-hana" class="more-row">
      <span class="more-date">2026.03</span>
      <span class="more-title">Hybrid BM25 + Vector Retrieval for SAP HANA Cloud</span>
      <span class="more-src">LinkedIn</span>
    </a>
    <a href="/blog/multimodal-embeddings" class="more-row">
      <span class="more-date">2026.04</span>
      <span class="more-title">Multimodal Embeddings: One Model, One Vector Space</span>
      <span class="more-src">LinkedIn</span>
    </a>
  </section>
</main>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .post-hero { position: relative; padding: 10rem 0 4rem; overflow: hidden; }
  .post-hero-bg { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1550751827-4bd374c3f58b?w=1920&q=80') center/cover no-repeat; filter: blur(8px) saturate(0.3) brightness(0.25); transform: scale(1.05); transition: filter var(--ease); }
  :global([data-theme="light"]) .post-hero-bg { filter: blur(8px) saturate(0.35) brightness(1.1); }
  .post-hero-overlay { position: absolute; inset: 0; background: var(--hero-overlay); mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0,0,0,0.3) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,1) 70%); -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0,0,0,0.3) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,1) 70%); }
  .post-hero-content { position: relative; z-index: 2; max-width: 720px; }
  .post-back { font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--text-lo); display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; margin-bottom: 2rem; transition: color 0.2s; text-decoration: none; }
  .post-back:hover { color: var(--ember); }
  .post-meta-top { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--text-lo); flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .source-badge { padding: 2px 8px; border-radius: 3px; border: 1px solid var(--ember-border); color: var(--ember); font-size: 0.65rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em; }
  .source-badge--sap { color: var(--gold); border-color: rgba(212,166,69,0.2); }
  .post-hero h1 { font-family: 'Libre Baskerville', serif; font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 3rem); font-weight: 400; line-height: 1.25; color: var(--text-hi); letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .post-hero h1 .em { color: var(--ember); font-style: italic; }
  .post-subtitle { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text); max-width: 560px; line-height: 1.8; }
  .post-tags-row { display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 1.5rem; }
  .post-tag { font-size: 0.65rem; padding: 3px 8px; border-radius: 4px; border: 1px solid var(--border); color: var(--text-lo); }
  .post-tag--ember { color: var(--ember); border-color: var(--ember-border); background: var(--ember-glow); }
  .post-tag--gold { color: var(--gold); border-color: rgba(212,166,69,0.2); background: var(--gold-dim); }

  .article { max-width: 720px; padding: 4rem 0 6rem; }
  .article h2 { font-family: 'Libre Baskerville', serif; font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 400; color: var(--text-hi); margin-top: 3rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .article h2:first-child { border-top: none; padding-top: 0; margin-top: 0; }
  .article p { font-family: 'Libre Baskerville', serif; font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.9; color: var(--text); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
  .article strong { color: var(--text-hi); font-weight: 600; }
  .article em { color: var(--ember); font-style: italic; }
  .article blockquote { border-left: 3px solid var(--blockquote-border); background: var(--blockquote-bg); padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; margin: 2rem 0; border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0; }
  .article blockquote p { font-style: italic; color: var(--text-hi); margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 0.92rem; }
  .article code { font-family: 'Iosevka', monospace; font-size: 0.88em; background: var(--code-bg); border: 1px solid var(--code-border); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 4px; color: var(--ember); }

  .features-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 1rem; margin: 2rem 0; }
  .feature-card { background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 1.5rem; }
  .feature-icon { font-size: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
  .feature-title { font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-hi); margin-bottom: 0.4rem; }
  .feature-desc { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--text); line-height: 1.6; }

  .code-block { background: var(--code-bg); border: 1px solid var(--code-border); border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.5rem 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; font-size: 0.82rem; line-height: 1.9; color: var(--text); }
  .code-label { font-size: 0.68rem; color: var(--text-lo); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; display: block; }
  .keyword { color: var(--ember); }

  .takeaway { background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--ember-border); border-radius: 10px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2.5rem 0; }
  .takeaway-label { font-size: 0.68rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--ember); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .takeaway ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
  .takeaway li { font-family: 'Libre Baskerville', serif; font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--text); padding: 0.5rem 0; padding-left: 1.2rem; position: relative; line-height: 1.7; }
  .takeaway li::before { content: '›'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: var(--ember); font-weight: 700; }

  .article-footer { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); padding-top: 2.5rem; margin-top: 3rem; }
  .article-footer-label { font-size: 0.68rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text-lo); margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .resource-links { display: flex; gap: 0.75rem; flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .original-link { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-hi); padding: 0.65rem 1.1rem; border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; transition: all 0.2s; text-decoration: none; }
  .original-link:hover { border-color: var(--ember-border); color: var(--ember); }
  .original-link--sap { color: var(--gold); }
  .original-link--gh { color: var(--ash); }

  .more-posts { padding: 4rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .more-posts-title { font-size: 0.72rem; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.1em; color: var(--text-lo); margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
  .more-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 90px 1fr auto; gap: 1.5rem; align-items: baseline; padding: 1.25rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s; text-decoration: none; }
  .more-row:hover { padding-left: 0.75rem; }
  .more-row:hover .more-title { color: var(--ember); }
  .more-date { font-size: 0.72rem; color: var(--text-lo); font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; }
  .more-title { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-hi); transition: color 0.2s; }
  .more-src { font-size: 0.65rem; color: var(--text-lo); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) { .features-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } .more-row { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 0.3rem; } .post-hero { padding: 8rem 0 3rem; } .resource-links { flex-direction: column; } }
</style>
